verses.text:
At that time, your enemies will make fun of you rich people;
\q2 they will ridicule you by singing this sad song about you:
\q1 'We Israelites are completely ruined;
\q2 Yahweh is taking our land from us,
\q1 and he will give it to those who capture us.'"
\q1

Your leader will enable them to leave the countries where they have been exiled;
\q2 he will lead them out of the gates of their enemies' cities,
\q2 back to your own country.
\q1 Your king will lead them;
\q2 it is I, Yahweh, who will be their king!"

So now it is as though night will descend on you prophets;
\q2 you will not receive any more visions.
\q1 It is as though the sun will set for you;
\q2 the time when you are greatly honored will end.
\q1

I did great things for your ancestors;
\q2 I brought them out of Egypt;
\q2 I rescued them from that land where they were slaves.
\q1 I sent Moses to lead them,
\q2 and his older brother Aaron and his older sister Miriam.
\q1

Everyone who honored God has disappeared from this land;
\q2 not one of them is left.
\q1 The people who are left are all murderers;
\q2 it is as though everyone is eager to kill his fellow countryman.
\q1

Yahweh, there is no God like you;
\q2 you forgive the sins that the people who have survived committed,
\q2 the people who belong to you.
\q1 You do not remain angry forever;
\q2 you are very happy to show us that you faithfully love us.
\q1
